---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	lang="en"
	title="Gandía & the Mediterranean — Tailor-made summer 2026 trips in Spain"
	description="We organise tailor-made multi-day holidays throughout summer 2026 on the Spanish Mediterranean — sea, mountain, food, your pace, your budget. With two extraordinary nights for the sky in mid-August: the Perseid meteor shower and the total solar eclipse on 12 August."
	otherLangHref="/es/"
	otherLangLabel="Español"
>
	<section class="hero-fullbleed" aria-label="Welcome">
		<img class="hero-bg" src="/images/cala-advocat.jpg" alt="A close-up of a heart drawn in the soft beach sand with a smaller doodle traced inside it — a quiet, sun-warm morning on the shore." />
		<div class="hero-scrim"></div>
		<div class="hero-content">
			<p class="hero-eyebrow">Summer 2026 · Spain's Mediterranean coast · EN · RO · ES</p>
			<h1 class="hero-title">Gandía <span class="accent">&amp; the Mediterranean</span></h1>
			<p class="hero-subtitle">
				We know this coast — the beaches, the calas, the mountain villages,
				the restaurants worth the drive. Tell us what you'd love;
				<strong>we share the information, plan the days, free up your time.</strong>
			</p>
			<div class="hero-actions">
				<a class="hero-cta" href="#contact">Plan my trip →</a>
				<a class="hero-scroll" href="#how-we-work">How we work ↓</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<aside class="eclipse-spotlight reveal" id="eclipse" aria-labelledby="es-title">
		<div class="eclipse-graphic" aria-hidden="true">
			<div class="corona"></div>
			<div class="moon"></div>
		</div>
		<div class="eclipse-text">
			<p class="es-eyebrow">12 August 2026 · 20:33 · The wow of the summer</p>
			<h2 id="es-title" class="es-title">A total solar eclipse — at sunset, on our coast.</h2>
			<p class="es-body">
				The first to cross mainland Europe in nearly thirty years. The path
				of totality runs just north of Gandía. <strong>We find you the
				perfect spot to watch it from</strong> — a quiet field, a cliff with
				a clear western horizon, a rooftop terrace — and if you'd rather not
				drive that evening, we take you ourselves.
			</p>
			<a class="es-cta" href="#contact">Reserve your eclipse evening →</a>
		</div>
	</aside>

	<section class="how-we-work reveal" id="how-we-work" aria-labelledby="hww-heading">
		<h2 id="hww-heading" class="hww-heading">How we work</h2>
		<div class="hww-grid">
			<article class="hww-card">
				<div class="hww-step">1</div>
				<h3>You tell us</h3>
				<p>Your dates, who's coming, what you'd love — slow beach days, mountain drives, the eclipse, family-friendly, somewhere quiet.</p>
			</article>
			<article class="hww-card">
				<div class="hww-step">2</div>
				<h3>We share what we know</h3>
				<p>The right beach for your party, the day's best restaurant, where to stand for the eclipse and the Perseids in mid-August, the weather to expect, what to skip.</p>
			</article>
			<article class="hww-card">
				<div class="hww-step">3</div>
				<h3>You get your time back</h3>
				<p>Lodging, transfers, bookings, the day-by-day plan. You arrive — we handle the logistics.</p>
			</article>
		</div>

		<div class="hww-services reveal">
			<h3 class="hww-services-heading">What we can help with</h3>
			<ul class="hww-services-list">
				<li>Car rentals</li>
				<li>Cruise charters</li>
				<li>Hotel bookings</li>
				<li>Airport transfers to your lodging</li>
				<li>Tailor-made itineraries</li>
				<li>Restaurant recommendations &amp; reservations</li>
				<li>Sightseeing routes</li>
				<li>Road cycling routes</li>
				<li>Concert tickets</li>
				<li>And other local activities — just ask</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="hww-24-7"><strong>We speak English, Romanian and Spanish.</strong></p>
			<p class="hww-24-7"><strong>And we're available 24/7.</strong></p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<p class="lead reveal">
		Between <strong>Valencia</strong> in the north and <strong>Benidorm</strong>
		in the south, the Valencian coast strings together nearly a hundred
		kilometres of fine pale sand, palm-lined promenades and small calas tucked
		under limestone cliffs. <strong>Gandía sits roughly in the middle</strong> —
		close enough to Valencia for a day in the city (an hour by train), close
		enough to Benidorm and the calas of the Costa Blanca for a quick run down
		the coast, and far enough from both to keep its own rhythm. Three
		kilometres of soft golden sand at <strong>Playa Norte</strong>, a walkable
		old town with the <strong>Palau Ducal</strong> at its heart, a working
		fishing harbour, and the dark hump of the Mondúver mountain rising
		inland — it's the kind of base you settle into for a week, not somewhere
		you pass through.
	</p>

	<p class="tailor reveal">
		<strong>Tell us your dates, your budget and what you'd like out of the
		trip — we organise the rest.</strong> Long beach days and lazy swims,
		mountain drives and hikes inland, food and wine, family-friendly
		resorts on the seafront, boutique hotels in the old town, a quiet
		<em>casa rural</em> up in the sierras — we put together the itinerary,
		book the lodging and transfers, and point you to what's worth your
		time on each day. You arrive; we handle the logistics.
	</p>

	<aside class="eclipse-card reveal" id="astronomy" aria-labelledby="astro-heading">
		<p class="eclipse-eyebrow">Astronomical phenomena · Summer 2026</p>
		<h2 id="astro-heading" class="astro-heading">Two rare nights for the sky</h2>
		<p>
			Mid-August brings two extraordinary nights to this coast.
		</p>
		<p>
			On <strong>12 August at 20:33 local</strong>, the Moon's shadow sweeps
			across Spain and finishes its run over the Mediterranean — a
			<strong>total solar eclipse at sunset</strong>, the first to cross
			mainland Europe in nearly thirty years. The path of totality runs
			just north of Gandía, over Valencia city, Sueca and Cullera. Totality
			lasts about a minute, with the Sun roughly four degrees above the
			sea. We tell you exactly where to stand for the clearest western
			horizon — or, if you'd rather not drive that evening, <strong>we take
			you there ourselves</strong>.
		</p>
		<figure class="eclipse-map">
			<img src="/images/eclipse-path-spain.jpg" alt="Map of Spain showing the path of totality of the 12 August 2026 solar eclipse — a dark diagonal band sweeping in from the Atlantic over Asturias, crossing Castilla y León, Aragón and Cataluña, and reaching the Mediterranean over Valencia, the Balearic Islands and beyond." />
			<figcaption>The path of totality across Spain on 12 August 2026 — the band sweeps in from the Atlantic, passes over Valencia and out into the Mediterranean. Gandía sits just south of the centreline, a short drive up the coast.</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<p>
			The same week — peaking on the nights of <strong>11–13 August</strong>
			— Earth crosses the dust trail of comet Swift–Tuttle and the sky
			lights up with the <strong>Perseid meteor shower</strong>, up to a
			hundred meteors an hour from a dark spot. We drive you ten minutes
			inland to a place away from the coastal lights, with a blanket and
			time. <em>Sun, then stars.</em>
		</p>
		<p>
			These two nights are a remarkable extra for travellers who join us in
			<strong>mid-August</strong>. The rest of the offer — beaches, calas,
			mountain villages, food, sport, family days — runs
			<strong>throughout summer 2026</strong>.
		</p>
	</aside>

	<p>
		<strong>Playa de Gandía is a beach built for slow days.</strong> Three
		kilometres of fine pale-gold sand stretch in a single gentle arc, edged by
		a palm-lined promenade and backed by the dark hump of the Mondúver
		mountain inland. The Mediterranean here stays shallow far out — you can
		walk a hundred metres before the water rises past your waist — and the
		sand is so soft it squeaks underfoot. In summer the light hangs late, the
		air stays warm well past sunset, and the promenade fills with families on
		their evening walk, children chasing footballs, paddle-tennis games on
		the sand. It's the kind of beach you don't want to leave.
	</p>

	<div class="home-gallery-3 reveal">
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/playa-gandia-wide.jpg" alt="Playa de Gandía at the end of the day — a wide sweep of fine golden sand stretching toward the horizon under a pastel pink-and-lavender sky, with the line of seafront buildings tucked to one side." />
			<figcaption>The long sweep of sand at the end of the day.</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/playa-gandia-day.jpg" alt="Playa de Gandía in the late afternoon — wide pale-gold sand, palm trees, and the long pedestrian promenade running beside the beach." />
			<figcaption>The palm-lined promenade beside the beach.</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/gandia-from-pier.jpg" alt="Looking back at Gandía from the long breakwater of the port — a paved walkway with railings stretches across the water toward the seafront skyline of the town, with the Mondúver and the coastal mountains rising behind." />
			<figcaption>The town from the breakwater, the Mondúver behind.</figcaption>
		</figure>
	</div>

	<p class="pull reveal">
		Sea or mountain — tell us what you love, and we'll plan the days around it.
	</p>

	<p>
		Some travellers come for the <strong>coast</strong> — fine pale sand and
		crystal-clear water, the wide family beaches of Gandía and Benidorm, and
		a long string of small hidden calas tucked under limestone cliffs
		further south, each with its own character. Lunches of fideuá and
		Valencian rice, late-afternoon swims off the rocks, snorkelling over
		clear water. Others would rather head <strong>inland</strong>, into the
		quiet sierras behind Alicante — rock-perched castles above turquoise
		reservoirs, high ridges, whitewashed mountain villages where the air
		cools after sunset and the stars come out properly. Tell us what kind
		of day you'd love; we'll match it to the right corner of the region.
	</p>

	<p class="reveal">
		<strong>We tailor the trip to your budget.</strong> Boutique hotels in
		the old town, a beachfront apartment for the family, a quiet
		<em>casa rural</em> up in the mountains, or a full-service resort with
		the pool by the door — we book the lodging, arrange transfers, and put
		together day trips worth your time. You arrive; we handle the logistics.
	</p>

	<section class="region-info reveal" aria-labelledby="region-heading">
		<h2 id="region-heading" class="region-heading">A few practical things about the region</h2>
		<div class="region-grid">
			<div class="region-item">
				<h3>Where</h3>
				<p>The Spanish Mediterranean, between Valencia city in the north and Alicante in the south. Gandía sits about an hour from each.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="region-item">
				<h3>Getting there</h3>
				<p>Valencia and Alicante international airports — around an hour by road from Gandía. Madrid is three hours by high-speed train. We arrange the transfers.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="region-item">
				<h3>Climate</h3>
				<p>Warm dry summers, around 28–32 °C in July and August, sea around 25 °C, gentle evenings. Rain is rare in summer.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="region-item">
				<h3>Language &amp; money</h3>
				<p>Spanish and Valencian; English widely spoken in tourist areas. Euro. Card accepted almost everywhere; a little cash useful in mountain villages.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<div class="home-gallery reveal">
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/guadalest.jpg" alt="El Castell de Guadalest, the iconic mountain village perched on a rock above the Guadalest valley." />
			<figcaption>El Castell de Guadalest — the inland Costa Blanca.</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/cala-moraig.jpg" alt="Cala del Moraig near Poble Nou de Benitatxell — a turquoise cove backed by tall limestone cliffs, the access road winding down through pine vegetation." />
			<figcaption>Cala del Moraig — vertical cliffs, deep clear water.</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/palau-ducal.jpg" alt="The Palau Ducal dels Borja in Gandía's old town, the former residence of the Borgia dukes." />
			<figcaption>Palau Ducal — the heart of Gandía's old town.</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/playa-gandia-shore.jpg" alt="Playa de Gandía, wide golden sand with gentle waves and a mountain cape on the southern horizon." />
			<figcaption>Playa de Gandía — our local beach.</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/sierra-bernia-view.jpg" alt="A sun-flooded coastal road on a high ridge between Altea and Calpe — the Mediterranean stretching away below, the white-stacked town of Altea Hills on the cliffs, and the Peñón de Ifach rising on the horizon." />
			<figcaption>From the ridge — the coast between Altea and Calpe.</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/chiringuito-morro.jpg" alt="A beachfront chiringuito with a thatched roof opening straight onto the sea — empty tables and chairs on a wooden deck, the Mediterranean and a rocky headland just beyond." />
			<figcaption>A quiet morning at a chiringuito by the sea.</figcaption>
		</figure>
	</div>

	<p class="signoff reveal">
		Tell us how many days, how many of you, and what kind of trip you have in
		mind. We'll do the rest.
	</p>

	<hr />

	<p class="credits">
		<strong>Image credits.</strong>
		Playa de Gandía at sunset — mfapanoramico,
		<a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Playa_de_Gandia,_atardecer_-_panoramio.jpg">Wikimedia Commons</a>,
		<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/">CC BY 3.0</a>.
		Playa de Gandía wide view — Marnal,
		<a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Platjanordgandia.jpg">Wikimedia Commons</a>,
		CC0 (public domain).
		Playa de Gandía promenade — Kazbadat,
		<a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gandia_Beach.jpg">Wikimedia Commons</a>,
		<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/">CC BY-SA 3.0</a>.
		El Castell de Guadalest — Rodriguillo,
		<a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Guadalest_-_Castillo_del_Rey.jpg">Wikimedia Commons</a>,
		public domain.
		Cala del Moraig — Diego Delso,
		<a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Cala_Moraig,_J%C3%A1vea,_Alicante,_Espa%C3%B1a,_2022-07-13,_DD_08-10_HDR.jpg">Wikimedia Commons</a>,
		<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/">CC BY-SA 4.0</a>.
		Palau Ducal de Gandía — Gafotas,
		<a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gandia.Palacio_ducal.JPG">Wikimedia Commons</a>,
		<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/">CC BY-SA 3.0</a>.
	</p>

	<style>
		/* Full-bleed hero */
		.hero-fullbleed {
			position: relative;
			width: 100vw;
			left: calc(-50vw + 50%);
			margin-top: -5.5rem;
			margin-bottom: 3.6rem;
			height: clamp(540px, 86vh, 760px);
			overflow: hidden;
			isolation: isolate;
		}
		.hero-bg {
			position: absolute;
			inset: 0;
			width: 100%;
			height: 100%;
			object-fit: cover;
			z-index: 0;
			transform: scale(1.04);
			transform-origin: 55% 55%;
			animation: ken-burns 26s ease-in-out infinite alternate;
			will-change: transform;
		}
		@keyframes ken-burns {
			0%   { transform: scale(1.04); transform-origin: 50% 60%; }
			100% { transform: scale(1.14); transform-origin: 60% 40%; }
		}
		.hero-scrim {
			position: absolute;
			inset: 0;
			z-index: 1;
			background: linear-gradient(180deg,
				rgba(20, 16, 12, 0.18) 0%,
				rgba(20, 16, 12, 0.40) 55%,
				rgba(20, 16, 12, 0.66) 100%);
		}
		.hero-content {
			position: absolute;
			inset: 0;
			z-index: 2;
			display: grid;
			align-content: center;
			padding: 5.5rem 1.8rem 3.5rem;
			color: #fff;
			text-shadow: 0 2px 14px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.32);
			animation: hero-rise 1.1s cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.7, 0.2, 1) 0.15s both;
		}
		.hero-content > * {
			max-width: 820px;
			margin-left: auto;
			margin-right: auto;
			width: 100%;
		}
		@keyframes hero-rise {
			from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(18px); }
			to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
		}
		.hero-eyebrow {
			display: flex;
			align-items: center;
			gap: 0.95rem;
			text-transform: uppercase;
			letter-spacing: 0.22em;
			font-size: 0.85rem;
			color: #f3d3a8;
			font-weight: 700;
			margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
		}
		.hero-eyebrow::before {
			content: "";
			flex: 0 0 auto;
			width: 2.6rem;
			height: 2px;
			background: #f3d3a8;
		}
		.hero-title {
			font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
			font-weight: 700;
			font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 7vw, 4.6rem);
			line-height: 1.05;
			margin: 0 auto 1.6rem;
			letter-spacing: -0.02em;
			color: #fff;
			text-align: left;
		}
		.hero-title .accent {
			color: #f3d3a8;
			font-style: italic;
			font-weight: 700;
		}
		.hero-subtitle {
			font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
			font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 1.9vw, 1.4rem);
			line-height: 1.5;
			color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
			margin: 0 auto 2.4rem;
			font-style: italic;
		}
		.hero-subtitle strong {
			font-style: normal;
			color: #fff;
			font-weight: 600;
		}
		.hero-actions {
			display: flex;
			flex-wrap: wrap;
			align-items: center;
			gap: 1.4rem 2rem;
			margin: 0 auto;
		}
		.hero-cta {
			display: inline-block;
			background: var(--accent);
			color: #fff;
			text-decoration: none;
			font-weight: 700;
			font-size: 1.02rem;
			padding: 0.95rem 1.8rem;
			border-radius: 999px;
			box-shadow: 0 10px 28px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.38);
			letter-spacing: 0.005em;
			transition: transform 0.18s ease, box-shadow 0.18s ease, background 0.18s ease;
		}
		.hero-cta:hover {
			background: #d97a36;
			transform: translateY(-2px);
			box-shadow: 0 16px 36px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.46);
		}
		.hero-scroll {
			color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
			text-decoration: none;
			font-size: 0.95rem;
			border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
			padding-bottom: 2px;
			letter-spacing: 0.02em;
			transition: color 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
		}
		.hero-scroll:hover {
			color: #f3d3a8;
			border-color: #f3d3a8;
		}

		/* Grouped home galleries (Playa Gandía 3-col + bottom 2x2) */
		.home-gallery,
		.home-gallery-3 {
			display: grid;
			gap: 0.9rem;
			margin: 2.4rem 0 3rem;
		}
		.home-gallery   { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
		.home-gallery-3 { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); margin-bottom: 5.8rem; }
		.home-gallery figure,
		.home-gallery-3 figure { margin: 0; }
		.home-gallery img,
		.home-gallery-3 img {
			width: 100%;
			height: 100%;
			aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
			object-fit: cover;
			border-radius: 8px;
			box-shadow: 0 4px 18px rgba(31, 27, 22, 0.10);
			display: block;
		}
		.home-gallery figcaption,
		.home-gallery-3 figcaption {
			font-size: 0.82rem;
			color: var(--muted);
			margin-top: 0.5rem;
			text-align: center;
			font-style: italic;
		}
		.home-gallery-3 { gap: 0.6rem; }
		.home-gallery   { gap: 0.6rem; }
		@media (max-width: 480px) {
			.home-gallery-3 figcaption,
			.home-gallery figcaption { font-size: 0.72rem; }
		}

		/* Region info card */
		.region-info {
			margin: 0 0 3rem;
		}
		.region-heading {
			font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
			font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.6vw, 1.85rem);
			font-weight: 700;
			letter-spacing: -0.01em;
			margin: 0 0 1.6rem;
			text-align: center;
			color: var(--accent);
		}
		.region-grid {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
			gap: 1.1rem;
		}
		.region-item {
			background: var(--paper);
			border: 1px solid var(--rule);
			border-radius: 10px;
			padding: 1.3rem 1.4rem 1.1rem;
			box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(31, 27, 22, 0.05);
		}
		.region-item h3 {
			font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
			font-size: 1.05rem;
			font-weight: 700;
			margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
			letter-spacing: -0.01em;
			color: var(--ink);
		}
		.region-item p {
			font-size: 0.94rem;
			color: var(--muted);
			margin: 0;
			line-height: 1.5;
		}
		@media (max-width: 640px) {
			.region-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
		}

		/* Eclipse spotlight (dramatic callout under hero) */
		.eclipse-spotlight {
			position: relative;
			margin: 0 0 3.6rem;
			padding: 2.4rem 2.2rem;
			border-radius: 14px;
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
			gap: 2.2rem;
			align-items: center;
			color: #fff;
			background:
				radial-gradient(ellipse at 78% 24%, rgba(245, 178, 88, 0.22) 0%, transparent 55%),
				radial-gradient(ellipse at 18% 82%, rgba(72, 56, 40, 0.5) 0%, transparent 60%),
				linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1410 0%, #2a1f15 100%);
			overflow: hidden;
			isolation: isolate;
			box-shadow: 0 14px 38px rgba(31, 27, 22, 0.22);
		}
		.eclipse-spotlight::before {
			content: "";
			position: absolute;
			inset: 0;
			background:
				radial-gradient(1.6px 1.6px at 16% 22%, rgba(255,255,255,0.75) 50%, transparent 100%),
				radial-gradient(1.3px 1.3px at 86% 18%, rgba(255,255,255,0.6) 50%, transparent 100%),
				radial-gradient(1.6px 1.6px at 28% 88%, rgba(255,255,255,0.55) 50%, transparent 100%),
				radial-gradient(1.2px 1.2px at 72% 80%, rgba(255,255,255,0.65) 50%, transparent 100%),
				radial-gradient(1.3px 1.3px at 96% 64%, rgba(255,255,255,0.5) 50%, transparent 100%),
				radial-gradient(1.3px 1.3px at 6% 56%, rgba(255,255,255,0.55) 50%, transparent 100%),
